input_str: With more cookbooks, television shows and stores dedicated exclusively to the culinary arts than ever before, you would think that we are a nation of gourmet chefs. Unfortunately, nothing could be further from the truth. As America's waistline expands, our knowledge surrounding cooking and nutrition seems to be shrinking away. Yes we all know someone that home-pickles, has mastered coq au vin and can whip but a soufflé in no time -- but that "culinarian"
